{"title":"Far Sulfonilureas (SU)","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Far Sulfonilureas (SU)-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Sulfonilureas\\N(SU)","guid":"V0YeSw2kFJF80rOOSXu5WQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Generalidades","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Historia: Primeros antidiabéticos orales usados en DM2.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Ventajas: Gran potencia, bajo costo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Desventajas: Hipoglicemia, menor eficacia en reducción de complicaciones CV y renales comparado con nuevos antidiabéticos.","guid":"VhCAaL-kW4sCgv9Bohdv4Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"0","text":"Mecanismo\\Nde Acción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• Estimulación de insulina: Se unen al receptor de SU en células B del páncreas → liberación de insulina.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"• Reducción de A1c: 1.0-2.0% (101).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"0","text":"Diferencias\\Nentre SU","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"• Dosis y uso en IR: Variabilidad notable (Tabla 6).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"• Potencia hipoglicemiante: Alta.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"• Estudio ADOPT: Glibenclamida ↓ glicemia rápidamente, pero falla pronto,\\Nrequiriendo intensificación de terapia (102).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"12","parent":"0","text":"SU Comunes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Glibenclamida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Segunda generación.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"• Alta potencia, vida media larga.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"• Elevado riesgo de hipoglicemias (especialmente en poblaciones vulnerables) (103).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"12","text":"• Glimepirida\\Ny Gliclazida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Menor riesgo de hipoglicemias.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Uso con cautela en ancianos o con ERC (104).","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"0","text":"Efectos\\NSecundarios","guid":"","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Ganancia de peso: Asociada al uso de SU (67).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Eventos CV Adversos: No aumento de mortalidad comparado con otros tratamientos (67, 103).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"0","text":"Contraindicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Insuficiencia hepática: Moderada y grave.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"• Insuficiencia renal: Etapa 3b a 5.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"• Déficit cognitivo, ancianos frágiles: ≥65 años o >70 años independientemente del estado funcional.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"• DM1 y diabetes secundaria a enfermedad pancreática.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"• Asociación con insulina: No recomendado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"23","text":"• Embarazo y lactancia: No aconsejado.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Resumen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"• Riesgo de hipoglicemias: Indicar con cautela.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"• No uso en: Pacientes ancianos o con ERC.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"• Suspensión al iniciar insulina.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":33,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Far Sulfonilureas (SU)-2024","id":"map_759","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Far Sulfonilureas (SU)-2024"}